<AbstractNarration>This project will capitalize on recent advancements in wave propagation theory by developing a suite of regional tomographic methods using the 3D sensitivities of finite-frequency body and surface waves across a regional seismic array.  The new methods will be applied to Iceland and will integrate presently separate seismic data sets.&lt;br/&gt;</AbstractNarration>
